=head1 DESCRIPTION

Provides you with the properties of the Call Analytics category you
specified in your request. This includes the list of rules that define
the specified category.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 CategoryName => Str

The name of the Call Analytics category. Category names are case
sensitive and must be unique within an Amazon Web Services account.


=head2 CreateTime => Str

The date and time the specified Call Analytics category was created.

Timestamps are in the format C<YYYY-MM-DD'T'HH:MM:SS.SSSSSS-UTC>. For
example, C<2022-05-04T12:32:58.761000-07:00> represents 12:32 PM UTC-7
on May 4, 2022.


=head2 InputType => Str

The input type associated with the specified category. C<POST_CALL>
refers to a category that is applied to batch transcriptions;
C<REAL_TIME> refers to a category that is applied to streaming
transcriptions.


=head2 LastUpdateTime => Str

The date and time the specified Call Analytics category was last
updated.

Timestamps are in the format C<YYYY-MM-DD'T'HH:MM:SS.SSSSSS-UTC>. For
example, C<2022-05-05T12:45:32.691000-07:00> represents 12:45 PM UTC-7
on May 5, 2022.


=head2 Rules => ArrayRef[L<Paws::Transcribe::Rule>]

The rules used to define a Call Analytics category. Each category can
have between 1 and 20 rules.


=head2 Tags => ArrayRef[L<Paws::Transcribe::Tag>]

The tags, each in the form of a key:value pair, assigned to the
specified call analytics category.



